               <p>RICHARD LANGTON. I am a <rs id="t18300916-116-viclabel615" type="occupation">merchant</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18300916-116-victim1039 t18300916-116-viclabel615"></join>. I was opposite Greenwood and Cox's army-agents, near the <placeName id="t18300916-116-crimeloc616">Horse-guards</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18300916-116-crimeloc616" type="placeName" value="Horse-guards"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18300916-116-crimeloc616" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18300916-116-off613 t18300916-116-crimeloc616"></join>, on Saturday last; I felt a twitch at my pocket - I turned, and saw the prisoner running about five yards from me; I pursued, and took him - he gave me the handkerchief; there were several boys round him.</p>
               <p>
                  <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="183009160061"></xptr>Prisoner. Q. Did you see me take the handkerchief? A. No.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18300916-116-person1040">
                  WILLIAM 
                  BLAND
               <interp inst="t18300916-116-person1040" type="surname" value="BLAND"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300916-116-person1040" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300916-116-person1040" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I took the prisoner, and have the handkerchief.(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. He was going along Parliament-street, and two boys were behind him; he went up a turning, and the boys followed him - I saw the handkerchief on the ground, took it up, and put it into my pocket; the gentleman came and said, "I want my handkerchief," and I gave it to him.</p>

